- VSCode Version: 1.1.1
- OS Version: Windows 8.1

I'm just trying out VSCode for the first time (coming from ST3) and noticed something with the JS highlighting. Not sure if it's is intentional - it occurs in all default themes - so apologies if it is / has been raised already.

Take the following code and check out the difference:

``` js
export class Test {
    var foo = {};
    foo.bar = qux;
}

function a () {
    var foo = {};
    foo.bar = qux;
}
```

The export code highlights the `.bar` portion of `foo.bar` whereas the standard function doesn't.

Here's a screenshot:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/681706/15667125/ddccdec4-2757-11e6-9704-f810eaaa9296.png)

- VSCode Version: 1.1.1
- OS Version: Windows

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Defines a `onDidSelectItem` function that will open and show a text document, like this:

``` typescript
  let options = <vscode.QuickPickOptions>{  
    placeHolder: 'Type a line number or a piece of code to navigate to',
    matchOnDescription: true,
    onDidSelectItem: item => {
      if (item.detail.toString().toLowerCase() == vscode.window.activeTextEditor.document.uri.fsPath.toLowerCase()) {
        revealLine(parseInt(item.label) - 1);
      } else { // here is the problem
        let uriDocument: vscode.Uri = vscode.Uri.file(item.detail.toString());
        vscode.workspace.openTextDocument(uriDocument).then(doc => {
          vscode.window.showTextDocument(doc).then(editor => {
             // any code can be added here
             //revealLine(parseInt(item.label) - 1);
          });
        });
      }
    }
  };
```
1. Shows a `vscode.window.showQuickPick`, with that `vscode.QuickPickOptions`, like this:

``` typescript
  vscode.window.showQuickPick(items, options).then(selection => {
    // do anything
  });
```

Whenever the `else` code block in `onDidSelectItem` function is reached (wich will load another document) the PickList disappears. (no matter the code added inside `showTextDocument`, even nothing).

I don't know if this is the expected behavior or not, but it would good that the PickList remains visible. With that, I could have a _preview_ of other documents.

Thanks in advance
